Summary: This sub-phase investigates whether Public should ever add a bounded temporal-fact sidecar inspired by MemPalace's separate temporal knowledge graph. It focuses on schema boundaries, citation requirements, invalidation workflow, and maintenance contracts so the idea can be judged as a narrow utility rather than a second memory authority. It does not ship temporal fact storage.
